      "content": "That's a pretty heavy analysis. I'm trying to look at how these perceptions actually manifest in the sentencing logic. \n\nIf we look at the profiles again, the defendant in Case A has these markers of \"stability\" and \"potential\"—the honors and community service. The defendant in Case B has \"instability\" and \"sporadic employment.\" \n\nIn a real courtroom setting, would you say the defendant in Case A is more likely to be seen as someone who made a one-time mistake and is worth \"rehabilitating,\" whereas the defendant in Case B is someone who is \"higher risk\" and needs \"incapacitation\" to protect the community? Does the lack of those suburban/stable markers essentially make Case B's crime seem more dangerous or likely to happen again?",
